com.versant.common.dataservice
Class VDSException

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Throwable
      java.lang.Exception
          com.versant.common.dataservice.VDSException
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class VDSException
extends java.lang.Exception

The methods in this dataservice package indicate errors by throwing an instance of the class VDSException. There is only one class of exception i.e. VDSException. The exceptions are differentiated on the basis of the error code that is embedded in each instance of VDSException. An interface is also provided to get the description of the error code. A single class to represent all the exceptions is efficient in the sense that only one class needs to be downloaded by clients(applets).

See Also:
VDSIErrorCode, Serialized Form
